Please lets be clear on one thing:<br>
<br>
<br>
The ONLY people that say one person is better or more deserving than another for Ragefire are the people enforcing the list.  The list IS making one person more deserving than another by definition.  #35 is more deserving than #36 ONLY because &quot;the list&quot; says so.  <br>
<br>
Do not spew any more nonsense that people that want to camp their own epic are the ones trying to say they are better than anyone else.  <br>
<br>
The ONLY people that have been uncivil are  people supporting the list.  Every time anyone questions the absolute authority of the list they get insulted and flamed... not by everyone, a lot of folks *do* recognize the list is a best-effort, unofficial thing.... but there is nobody threatening to destroy the list or to killsteal an existing camp.  Nobody is calling the list greedy selfish bastards either, closest to that is pointing out the folks that started the list got the jump on other folks getting stuck in the 40's.  <br>
<br>
If insults and flames are how you intend to enforce a monopoly on Ragefire... it will fail sooner or later.  All it takes is one person with a decent guild who decides the hassle of camping their own epic outweighs the hassle of waiting 6 months+ for a chance.   The list being populated with elitists  more attracted to the power trip of owning the spawn than in actually avoiding conflict makes that more and more likely.<br>
<br>
Trying to set in stone a list over 40 clerics long is insane.  At this point any cleric starting the game today *should* get to skyfire as soon as they can find someone to safely guide them there to reserve their spot.   Looks like you get 3-5 clerics added to the list for every rage dead.   Figure out that math...  The list is only going to get worse if you don't adress that.  <br>
<br>
Honestly keeping the list down to something less than 10 and randoming the last spot when a spot opens is the closest thing to a working system I could see lasting.  This has been brought up in a few forms before and shot down. <p>Gurunt Bangoo <Wraith>
