<br>
You might wanna take that to <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://pub11.ezboard.com/fquelliousclericsfrm1&quot;">this forum</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> but I'll address what I see as the first two failings of that system.. When (if ) you post if over there I'll see what I can do about finding the others.  <br>
<br>
Random for all slots past N (you had 10, Yinta's original number was 2 - the principle is the same)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  When does the random happen? </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  When Rage dies?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  so - to get the opportunity to RANDOM for Nth spot in the list, I have to CAMP Ragefire with the cleric that's camping him.     You don't see a problem with that?  With the current numbers used as an example, I'd have to camp for (41-10 = 31 folks, assuming random probablility (i'm a bit rusty on this one but), I'll need about 1/2 the number of other rollers for an &quot;average&quot; chance of  getting it)   15 tries at Ragefire.. (assuming of course, that the number of oppoenents does not  change)<br>
<br>
I have a decent expection that I'll have to camp Ragefire 15 times before I win the roll to get in the list.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  15 times.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
if i don't camp EVERY one, but just /random at the ones I can make it to, of course, this time in increased by how many I miss.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  On a selected day at a selected time?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->    What about the people that cannot MAKE that selected date or time routinely (assuming they can arrange to be free when they get the opportunity to camp him).   If they cannot be there, you've simply denied them the opportunity to get the camp at all.  I think Verant would frown on that.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  /random</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
What about the poor schmuck that NEVER wins rolls?  No matter when you pick to have the random, it is possible (and given an ever increasing supply of opponents to roll against, likely) that some cleric will never be &quot;allowed&quot; to get in the list.  I think Verant would frown on that.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Yeah, it's shooting down your idea, because I think it has a couple of flaws that makie it almost as bad as FFA and considerably worse than the list (equitably managed).  However,  I'm just one voice.  Take your proposal <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://&quot;http://pub11.ezboard.com/fquelliousclericsfrm1&quot;">there</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and see if perhaps the other clerics agree more with you than me.  Oh, and tell all the clerics you see about it.<br>
